                     <interp inst="t18180506-23-defend240" type="age" value="15"></interp>
                  </persName>
               
             was indicted for <rs id="t18180506-23-off127" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18180506-23-off127" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18180506-23-off127" type="offenceSubcategory" value="shoplifting"></interp>
               stealing, on the <rs id="t18180506-23-cd128" type="crimeDate">11th of April</rs>
                     <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t18180506-23-off127 t18180506-23-cd128"></join>, one snuff-box, value 10s., and six watch-cases, value 10s., the goods of 
                     
                        <persName id="t18180506-23-victim242" type="victimName">
                           James 
                           Carolan
                        <interp inst="t18180506-23-victim242" type="surname" value="Carolan"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18180506-23-victim242" type="given" value="James"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18180506-23-victim242" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18180506-23-off127 t18180506-23-victim242"></join>
                     </persName>
                     
                  , privately in his shop
            </rs>.</p>
               <p>JAMES CAROLAN. I am a <rs id="t18180506-23-viclabel129" type="occupation">watchmaker</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18180506-23-victim242 t18180506-23-viclabel129"></join>, and live in <placeName id="t18180506-23-crimeloc130">Red Lion-street, Holborn</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18180506-23-crimeloc130" type="placeName" value="Red Lion-street, Holborn"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18180506-23-crimeloc130" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18180506-23-off127 t18180506-23-crimeloc130"></join>. On the 11th of April, about seven o'clock in the morning, I found the prisoner in custody in the shop, and the property in a chair.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18180506-23-person243">
                  JOHN 
                  ARTHUR
               <interp inst="t18180506-23-person243" type="surname" value="ARTHUR"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18180506-23-person243" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18180506-23-person243" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am an upholsterer, and live two doors from the prosecutor. I heard the cry of Stop thief! stopped the prisoner, and took him to the shop. He sat in a chair, and shoved the watch-cases into it. I saw him throw the snuff-box into the fire-place; he then said,"Now you may search me."</p>
               <p>(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18180506-23-person244">
                  SARAH 
                  GARDMAN
               <interp inst="t18180506-23-person244" type="surname" value="GARDMAN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18180506-23-person244" type="given" value="SARAH"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18180506-23-person244" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I live opposite the prosecutor. His servant was opening the shutters - A boy was looking through the windows, while the prisoner went in, opened the drawer, and took out the watch-cases. I gave the alarm, and he was stopped.</p>
               <p>GUILTY. Aged 15.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18180506-23-verdict131" type="verdictDescription">
